Reads file recorded with the acquisition script
Bandpass filtering. The signal is filtered in a large alpha/beta [8 30] Hz range.

Overview This scenario should be used to train the LDA classifier used to detect left / right hand movements Just configure the Generic Stream Reader box to point to the last file you recorded with scenario 1-acquisition or 4-online and fast forward this scenario. At the end of the training, you will have an estimation of the classifier performance printed in the console. If this performance is lower than 65%, just run a new 1-acquisition session to have better results.

Then comes the feature extraction part. Then the Stimulation Based Epoching box is used to select four seconds of signal half a second after the instruction was shown to the user. The signal is then splitted in blocks of 1 second every 16th second and the logarithmic band power is computed thanks to the two Simple DSP and the Signal Average boxes. The matrices can then be converted in feature vectors. note: depending on what frequency range reacts best for the subject, you may have to tune this part of the scenario note: whatever change you do on this scenario, don't forget to do the same on the CSP trainer script

The Classifier Trainer boxes produces three configuration files at the end of the experiment which will be used during online sessions. When the training is completed the box outputs a stimulation OVTK_StimulationId_TrainCompleted to stop the scenario through a Player Controller
The CSP spatial filters produced in the previous scenario is used prior to the feature extraction.
